Officials had feared it would take eight months to find the money to remove the wrecked boat. The state found a quicker solution: Make the owner do it.<ql>
<ql>
<m1><qr>
<styl>CUT,4<ql>
<m0>LONNIE TIMMONS III<m0> / Herald Staff<qr>
<m1><ue5><m0>GOING, GOING . . . GONE:<m0> A boat that foundered in the Intracoastal Waterway near Hallandale Beach Boulevard in September finally is gone, lifted out piece by piece by divers and a crane. The boat's owner said its bilge pumps were damaged in a robbery attempt.<ql>
<m4> SPACE AVAILABLE ON LAST LINE IS 1p10 <m1><ue5><ql>
